everything in computer science can be made if you know 3 concepts:
-Variables
-repetition
-selection

C++ - strongly typed language 
    types - special keywords that indicate something is a specific type 
    variables - lots of different types
    categories of types
        numbers
            int -/+
            floating point - fractional numbers - "float"
            unsigned only positive can go twice as long 
            double
        other
            char - only one character 
            string - 0 or more characters 
                1 - int
                '1' - char
                "1" string
            bool - true or false
            s
